<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="507" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,759,1850,1903]" lastBlockId="8.[806,1421,478,531]" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis box="[144,262,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is closely similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nesocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ranomafanaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">N. ranomafanaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the reduced or absent apical processes of the aedeagal shaft and the absence of forewing crossvein r-m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1367,1375,519,531]" fontSize="5" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">1</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[806,1422,570,776]" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis box="[806,942,571,592]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">Description:</emphasis>
Length of male, 
<quantity box="[1180,1315,570,592]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699999999999999" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="507" unit="mm" value="4.699999999999999" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="4.6">4.6–4.8 mm</quantity>
; female, 
<quantity box="[806,874,601,623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="507" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[806,1422,570,776]" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">
External characters and coloration as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nesocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ranomafanaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">N. ranomafanaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[806,1422,570,776]" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">
Male genitalia closely resembling those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nesocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ranomafanaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="507">N. ranomafanaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but aedeagal shaft with processes absent or reduced to tiny lobes.
</paragraph>
